The Herald Takudzwa Chitsiga Sports Reporter
ZIFA Harare Province Football League will this month hold a seminar aimed at appraising lower division teams on the FIFA/CAF Club Licensing requirements, among several other issues. The seminar, is meant for club secretaries, and administrators, who will be expected to understand the ZIFA rules and regulations to be presented by national technical director Wilson Mtekede. Some of the issues to be covered will include budgets, club management, player representation, the laws of the game, among several others. ZIFA Harare Province Football League chairman, Robert Tembo, said they were going to hold the seminar on May 10 and 11 in the capital.